  "title": "PLC Control Engineer (Marine Automation)",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a <strong>Marine and Offshore Industry.</strong> Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a <strong>PLC Control Engineer </strong>to be part of their Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the <strong>West </strong>- easily accessible.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><p><ul><li>Design and develop green marine solutions aligned with the company’s sustainability and business objectives</li><li>Set up and manage test laboratories to facilitate development, experimentation, and validation of electrical propulsion systems.</li><li>Develop PLC software and algorithms for advanced marine electrical propulsion solutions.</li><li>Produce comprehensive documentation, including software architecture, logic flow, test procedures, quality control protocols, and other supporting materials.</li><li>Participate in and support vessel commissioning activities for systems with similar configurations.</li></ul></p></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Min engineering degree in relevant discipline</li><li>Basic experience in software development skills particularly in equipment controls</li><li><li>Knowledge in power electronics, motor drives, marine propulsion systems is a plus</li></li></ul><p><br /><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em></p><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em><br /></p><p><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em></a></p><p><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em></p><p><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em></p><p><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
